ement-3fb9b3c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Rectus Sheath Hematoma<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-cd18d2d elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"cd18d2d\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-fcec305\" data-id=\"fcec305\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-00a9e26 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"00a9e26\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Basics<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Hematoma within the Rectus Sheath<\/li><li>Most Common Cause: Injury to <strong>Epigastric Vessel Branches<\/strong><ul><li>Most Are Spontaneous &amp; Not from Trauma<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Risk Factors: Female\/Elderly (Smaller Muscle) &amp; Anticoagulation<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Presentation<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Painful Abdominal Mass<\/li><li><em>Fothergill\u2019s Sign<\/em> \u2013 Does Not Cross Midline &amp; Does Not Change with Flexion<ul><li>Hernias are Generally More Painful\/Prominent with Rectus <strong>Flexion<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Carnett\u2019s Sign<\/em> \u2013 Point of Maximal Tenderness Does Not Change from Supine to Sitting<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Types<\/strong> <a class=\"button\" style=\"background-color: #193556; padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 2px;\" href=\"#MN\">Mn <\/a><\/p><ul><li>Type I \u2013 Small, Confined to Rectus, Does Not Cross Midline<\/li><li>Type II \u2013 Confined to Rectus, <strong>Crosses Midline<\/strong><ul><li>Dissects Along Transversalis Fascial Plane<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Type III \u2013 Large, <strong>Not Confined<\/strong><ul><li>Usually<strong> Below Arcuate Line<\/strong> (Severe Bleeding \u2013 No Aponeurosis to Contain)<\/li><li>Often See Blood in Prevesical Space of Retzius<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Diagnosis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Dx: CT or US<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Stable: <strong>Observation<\/strong><\/li><li>Unstable or Enlarging: IR Angioembolization<\/li><li>Surgery<ul><li>Procedure: Surgical Evacuation &amp; Vessel Ligation<\/li><li>Indications:<ul><li><strong>Skin Necrosis<\/strong><\/li><li>Unstable or Enlarging with Failure of Angioembolization<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Incision: Midline or Paramedian to Expose the Posterior Sheath (Avoid Entering the Peritoneum)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-6c8f6b2\" data-id=\"6c8f6b2\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9e8d9fe elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"9e8d9fe\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10199 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Rectus-Sheath-Hematoma.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Rectus-Sheath-Hematoma.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Rectus-Sheath-Hematoma-300x242.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Rectus Sheath Hematoma on CT <sup>1<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-b856f41 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"b856f41\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div cla